            <Abstract ID="Abs1" Language="En">
              <Heading>Abstract</Heading>
              <Para>The second order approach of local influence (see [15]) is developed and applied to Cox’s proportional hazards model, and compared with Cook's local influence approach (see [6] and [13]) which was used in this model. To study local influence, we perturb not only all cases simultaneously, but also cases individually to obtain “direction curvature” in direction<Emphasis Type="Italic">l</Emphasis> and “curvature” for single case. Some examples are used to illustrate these methods.</Para>
            </Abstract>
